              <p>Hello!</p>
              <p>Surely you didn't just happen to be here? And I came to find out how to create a circle correctly in CSS?</p>
              <P>There are many ways to do this! But I'll show you the simplest and most importantly the easiest way.</P>
              <P>1. Let's create a block with a height and width of 200 pixels. And we'll give it a color.</P>

<!-- ************************************** -->
<pre><code><span class="lang">html</span>
  &lt;div class="circle"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  <span class="lang">CSS</span>
.circle {
  width: 200 px;
  height: 200 px; 
  background-color: rgb(16, 118, 207);
}</code></pre>
<!-- ************************************** -->
              <div class="circle200px"></div>
              <P>2. Great, but our block is shaped like a square, not a circle. To do this, in CSS styles, you need to register border-radius with an internal value of 50%.</P>
<!-- ************************************** -->
<pre><code>
  <span class="lang">CSS</span>
.circle{
  border-radius: 50%;
}</code></pre>
<!-- ************************************** -->
                <div class="circle200px __br50"></div>
              <P>Great, we got a circle on pure CSS.  And for this we needed a bit of code.</P>
              <P>Now you know more!</P>
